        <abstract> 
<p>The Zoological Garden has only one old adult male of <hi rend="italic">Limulus</hi>. When there were females, eggs were <hi rend="italic">never</hi> observed.</p>  
<p>Encloses a separate letter [formerly <hi rend="doubleUnderline">7071</hi>] about AD’s scheme [for a zoological station].</p> 
            <p>Suggests AD be cautious [in his work]. "Caution is almost the soul of science."</p>
        </abstract>
